reviews.text: I ordered a fried hofan, it was too greasy like the hofan was soaked in oil. And the food tastes below average

Maybe a bit pricy in that area but not really expensive compared with restaurants in Hong Kong. I have been trying this restaurant for 10 years. The food is always of great value and the coconut drink is the best I have ever tried in this world.

Absolutely good value Thai eatery! The place is crowded even during late night ie 10pm and the Thai food are so yum. Particularly enjoy the Pork Rib Rice which costs around hkd55 and the portion is really huge, and the sauce was super yummy and addictive. Not really spicy though the red color was fairly bright.
Fast n reasonable price

A bit pricey for Thai food but I love this place in Tai Hang. The minced pork with basil is excellent. Great service also. Lunch is actually a great value so go for that instead of dinner if you are budget-conscious. Noodle dishes are also great.
